        Official Singles Chart on 31/7/2020

        31 July 2020 - 6 August 2020

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UKs biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        UK Chart Thoughts part 2:

        Someone You Loved: I hated this song when this song came out and still hate it now that voice is like nails on a chalkboard its that bad

        Take Care of You: now the only song Ive ever really known is her biggest hit Ghost back a few years ago but Ive heard Yours and her collab with Sigala in We Got Love too and thats pretty good and this song is also pretty awesome I like the beat and her voice is amazing as always and the sentiment in taking care of someone you love is very sweet overall its a great song

        Take You Dancing: now this may enter the hot 100 so Ill try to keep it brief but overall its a great song the beat is pretty good & Im really glad Jason is back in the mainstream with this and Savage Love

        Rain: now this song is a frigging banger Ive heard of Aitch before on the remix of Ed Sheerans Take me Back to London with Stormzy and Jaykae and hes a pretty good rapper and he has a good flow and technical skill and he has good chemistry with his collaborators as seen here with AJ Tracey.

        This song is so good the production provided by Tay Keith is very good the piano added in to that trap beat and Aitch and AJ are killing it on this track their verses are on point and they have good interplay and are having fun which is awesome overall its a great song

        Un Dia (One Day): ill have more to say on the hot 100 when it comes out because this will well crack through the folklore bomb no sweat but this song is pretty great. The beat is good and Dua sounds amazing & J Balvin and Bad Bunny are great as usual.

        Lose Somebody: its so weird to not see One Republic on the charts anymore I feel like they have a hit song every couple of years to stay relevant and this song with Kygo is pretty good the beat is good and Ryan Tedder sounds good as usual its a decent song overall

        TKN: I love latin music so much and even I like latin trap and reggaeton some of my faves include Natti Natasha, Anitta, Becky G, J Balvin, Maluma, Nicky Jam & even heavyweights like Enrique Iglesias, Shakira, Daddy Yankee, Pitbull, J-Lo and many others and I like Rosala as well I love Yo Ti Tu Mi with Ozuna and this one is pretty good too . I like the latin trap beat and both Rosala and Travis Scott sound great its a decent song its not my favorite overall but its good

        Giants: I love Dermot Kennedys music some of my faves include Lost, Outnumbered and Boston Taylor actually introduced me to his music thanks to her playlists that she posts on Spotify & Apple Music. This song is amazing I love the upbeat production and instrumentation and Dermots voice sounds great as usual definitely gonna be a song for my summer playlist

        Own It: This has been one of my favorite songs from last year. Ive been a fan of Stormzy since he showed up on the remixes of Power by Little Mix & Shape of You by Ed Sheeran and speaking of Ed Take Me Back to London was another good song they did together and this song as well .

        I love the beat provided by Burna Boy its fun and dark at the same time. Stormzys verses are so good hes probably one of the best Britishs rappers around right now and Ed sounds amazing in his verse and provided some great backing vocals too. Overall a great song Im sad it never gained any traction in the US.

        Say Something: Im such a HUGE fan of Kylie Minogue I mean if we are looking at a queen of pop on an international scale then (with all respect to Madonna) Kylie would of course be it. Some of my favorites are Come into My World, Get Out of My Way, Stop Me From Falling with Gente De Zona, Timebomb, All The Lovers, I Should be So Lucky, Spinning Around & of course Love at First Sight, Locomotion & Cant Get You Out of my Head the hits are just endless and with a 30+ plus year career under her belt she certainly can do no wrong at this point .

        I just love the song I love that shes going disco with her next record (simply titled DISCO) after doing a country folk EDM-ish sound on her last record Golden. Say Something certainly does the job right here the disco groove is perfection, I love the percussion, the synth touches with the added guitar riff its blended so well with Kylies voice which is amazing as always disco certainly fits her like a glove and the lyrics about finding the courage to say something to the one you love is simplistic but sweet at the same time. Overall its one of my favorites outside of Folklore

        Nobodys Love: this might end up on the hot 100 too so this will be brief but simply put Im sick of Maroon 5 always chasing trends and relevancy like the song is just bland and generic.

        Break Up Song: another favorite from Little Mix. I love the fast almost pop rock beat, the group sounds amazing as usual and Little Mix certainly knows how to make break up songs like Shout Out to My Ex and No More Sad Songs and this is no exception. This song is pretty decent all round.

        Shotgun: Im surprised this didnt become another hit for George Ezra after the highly successful Budapest from a few years back. This song is true indie folk at its finest. I love the indie alternative production and instrumentation its fun and upbeat and Georges voice is so rich and soothing and the lyrics apparently describing a trip where he spent most of his time relaxing and just having fun and I think that its pretty cool its basically a song about living life to the fullest and enjoying the little moments. Its a great song

        Memories: the song is in the pile of okay Maroon 5 songs but its certainly not their best nuff said...

        And thats part 2 of my thoughts on this chart sorry for the lateness again btw I just had a 7 day stretch at work done and now Im exhausted thank god im off tomorrow anyways hope yall like it

        UK CHART THOUGHTS:

        Sorry Im so late with this: So heres my thoughts on the UK chart I got a lot to say because most of these songs are either songs I havent heard before or in a while or songs that were on the hot 100 for a time but I havent given my thoughts on it. So this might be in 2 parts haha so here we go:

        Head & Heart: so this has been introduced to me by Piran (thank you man) and this song is literally my new fave outside of Folklore. The beat is banging its so fun and catchy and the lyrics are decent too and vocally they sound great overall its a fun summer dance song and Im glad its a number one hit in the UK lets hope it crosses the Atlantic soon and Im sure it will given the success of Roses.

        Lighter: another fun dance song (EDM must be very popular there) it has a fun beat, Ella Henderson (whos uncredited sadly) is amazing vocally and KSI has a pretty good rap verse with that added trap beat in the middle and the lyrics are decent but I mean its a dance song so its not really gonna matter haha overall a great song.

        Only You Freestyle: you know with all the songs involving Drake Im surprised this didnt get any attention in the states its somewhat popular in Canada (which is typical given hes Canadian) but Im glad its successful in the UK because Headie One is a UK drill and trap artist and honestly I dont mind this I love the trap drill inspired beat and Drake has a good verse and rides the beat well its the best Ive heard from him since Nice For What honestly and Headie One is a pretty good rapper honestly I really should explore drill music a little more it sounds pretty good.

        West Ten: this song is pretty good. I think AJs rapping technique is impressive and I love Mabels music (Dont Call Me Up is a bop and I love Cigarette with RAYE & Stefflon Don) and she sounds great in this song and the beat is actually pretty great too

        Is this what drill is?? What classifies a song as drill?? Because the beat is very fast but it has some sort of eerie feel with a hint of trap can Piran or any other person from the UK explain that because I know its not really a huge genre here across the pond Im interested

        Secrets: Now Ive heard of both these artists before. Regard obviously had that big hit this year with his remixed version of Jay Seans Ride It thanks to TikTok which is a decent dance hit and Ive heard of RAYE before with songs like again Cigarette, Love Me Again with Jess Glynne and my favorite Decline with Mr. Eazi (that really used that Ja Rule, Ashanti sample of Im Always On Time very well)

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (31/07/2020 - 06/08/2020)

        (Negative)

        1) No Rain On Me is on ACR! :(

        2) Kings & Queens is starting to fall fast now! Oh well, at least it became a Top 20 hit here.

        (Mixed)

        1) Lighter debuted in the Top 5 on the overall chart & reached #1 on sales! The song is definitely growing on me, but I really wish Ella Henderson got an official credit here.

        2) Holiday debuted lower than first anticipated! I can tolerate Little Mix way more than most regulars here, but this song just did nothing much for me at all.

        3) The chart show was reduced to 45 minutes due to Radio 1s weekend of EDM! I mean, come on I enjoy the genre a lot, but 70 whole hours of it?!

        4) Among the DJ Khaled songs, Greece held up way better than Popstar! The former is definitely the better of the two collaborations, but thats honestly not saying much.

        5) Hallucinate still isnt in the Top 40! I think itll definitely get there next week though.

        6) My Future by Billie Eilish will probably get a huge debut in the next chart! The transition was interesting, but the first half of the song needs to grow on me.

        7) Secrets & Dinner Guest both dropped out of the Top 10!

        8) Mood Swings re-entered the chart out of nowhere! I remember giving it a slightly positive review, but its not Pop Smokes best.

        (Positive)

        1) Head & Heart remains #1 for a second week! I dont think any amount of overplay could make me tired of hearing this, haha.

        2) One of Taylors best songs of all-time just about debuts in the Top 10, that being Exile with Bon Iver!

        3) As Cardigan & The 1 both made it too, Taylors total number of Top 10 singles in the UK is now up to 16! For the first time in her career, she makes three simultaneous appearances in the region.

        4) She also secured her fifth consecutive #1 album (shes topped the chart there with every album for one week since Red from back in 2012).

        5) Party Girl dropped back, even with the release of the EP! Sorry to any fans, but this song is really boring in my opinion.

        6) Dancing In The Moonlight moved up five places to a new peak of #16! Hopefully itll be in the Top 10 soon.

        Have a good weekend everybody! ;)
